<section id="itsm_id">
  <title>id
    <?oxy_custom_start type="oxy_content_highlight" color="255,198,140"?>[problem]<?oxy_custom_end?></title>

  <para>Identifier - the <code>id</code> attribute from the <code>http://www.w3.org/XML/1998/</code>
    namespace is used to identify a <olink targetdoc="../../elements/itsm/itsm_locQualityIssues.xml"
      targetptr="itsm_locQualityIssues"><code>its_locQualityIssues</code></olink>
    <?oxy_custom_start type="oxy_content_highlight" color="255,255,0"?>array
    element<?oxy_custom_end?> or <olink targetdoc="../../elements/itsm/itsm_provenanceRecords.xml"
      targetptr="itsm_provenanceRecords"><code>its_provenanceRecords</code></olink>
    <?oxy_custom_start type="oxy_content_highlight" color="255,255,0"?>array element<?oxy_custom_end?>
    <?oxy_custom_start type="oxy_content_highlight" color="255,198,140"?>[problem: there is no id
    property on its_provenanceRecords as of the current JLIFF schema 2.1, should add as in
    its_locQualityIssues wrapper object that has "id" and "items"?]<?oxy_custom_end?>.</para>

  <para><?oxy_custom_start type="oxy_content_highlight" color="140,255,140"?><emphasis>Contains:</emphasis>
    string.<?oxy_custom_end?></para>
  <para><emphasis>Value description:</emphasis>
    <?oxy_custom_start type="oxy_content_highlight" color="255,255,0"?>NCNAME<?oxy_custom_end?></para>

  <para><emphasis>Default value:</emphasis> undefined</para>

  <para><emphasis>Used in:</emphasis><olink
      targetdoc="../../elements/itsm/itsm_locQualityIssues.xml" targetptr="itsm_locQualityIssues"
        ><code>its_locQualityIssues</code></olink>
    <?oxy_custom_start type="oxy_content_highlight" color="255,255,0"?>array
    elements<?oxy_custom_end?> and <olink targetdoc="../../elements/itsm/itsm_provenanceRecords.xml"
      targetptr="itsm_provenanceRecords"><code>its_provenanceRecords</code></olink>
    <?oxy_custom_start type="oxy_content_highlight" color="255,255,0"?>array
    elements<?oxy_custom_end?>.</para>
  <warning>
    <para>Since the ITS Module reuses the W3C namespace <code>http://www.w3.org/2005/11/its</code>
      it cannot use <code>xs:NMTOKEN</code> identifiers as the <firstterm>XLIFF Core</firstterm> or
      other <firstterm>Modules</firstterm>. Implementers need to be aware that
        <code><?oxy_custom_start type="oxy_content_highlight" color="255,198,140"?>xs:ID<?oxy_custom_end?></code>
      has to be globally unique.</para>
  </warning>
  
  
